https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/tech-news/8%20chan-owner-ordered-appear-congress-next-month-n1042426

>8chan owner ordered to appear before Congress next month
>8chan, which has been connected to numerous mass shootings in recent months, has struggled to stay online in recent days since one of its major service providers, Cloudflare, ceased doing business with it.
>Jim Watkins, who acquired the website in 2016, has been ordered to appear before the committee on Sept. 5 at 9:30 a.m. ET.

If you're poor and can't afford parents to sign your permission slip you can livestream the excursion on c-span or one of the many kiketube anons.

Still reckons he'll bring it back online after
